<p>
  Democratic Justice is built to show its work. That standard applies to this site too.
</p>

<p>
  We do not use this site to build an advertising profile around readers. If you read a story here, we are not trying to follow you across the web or sell your attention to a data broker.
</p>

<h2>What the site stores</h2>
<p>
  This site stores your edition preference in your browser so it can remember day or night mode. That setting stays on your device unless you clear it. We also serve our fonts locally, so the site does not call out to Google Fonts or similar providers just to render text.
</p>

<h2>Email and correspondence</h2>
<p>
  If you email us, we receive the information you send, including your address and anything in your message. We use that information to reply, follow up, and keep a record of correspondence.
</p>

<p>
  If you subscribe, the signup form is handled by Buttondown. Buttondown receives the email address you enter and manages delivery, unsubscribes, and subscription records for the list.
</p>

<h2>Hosting and security</h2>
<p>
  The site is served through third-party infrastructure providers, including Cloudflare. Those providers may process basic request data, security logs, and network information to keep the site online and protect it from abuse.
</p>

<h2>Analytics</h2>
<p>
  We are choosing privacy-first analytics over ad tech and reader profiling. If site analytics are enabled, they will be limited to aggregate measurement and this page will name the provider and explain what is collected.
</p>

<h2>Questions</h2>
<p>
  If you have questions about privacy or want to reach us about your data, email <a href="mailto:{{ site.contactEmail }}">{{ site.contactEmail }}</a>.
</p>
